Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  plans to sell
yen-denominated uridashi bonds that mature in Aug. 2015,
according to a filing today with  Japan â€™s finance ministry.  The lender also plans to sell two-year uridashi bonds
denominated in dollars, Australian dollars, and rand, according
to the document. The terms of the sale will be set early next
month.  Uridashi bonds are debt issued outside Japan for sale
